  "title": "CNC Machinist",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><ul><li>To perform CNC machine settings and operations.</li><li>Read and interpret technical drawings, schematics, and CAD models.</li><li>Load and unload materials into machines.</li><li>Monitor machine performance and make adjustments to ensure parts meet required\ntolerances.</li><li>Perform routine maintenance and minor repairs on machines.</li><li>Inspect finished parts for quality, accuracy, and conformity to specifications.</li><li>Maintain a clean and safe work environment.</li><li>Collaborate with team members and supervisors to meet production goals.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>WSQ Higher Certificate or equivalent - Field of Study in Engineering, Manufacturing & Related Trades n.e.c.</li><li>Relevant CNC machining experience in precision engineering industry preferred.</li><li>At least 2 year(s) of working experience in the related field is required for\n     this position.</li></ul>",
